 Dutywa - Dutywa police arrested a 27-year-old man on Tuesday morning for theft out of the motor vehicle of German tourists. "It is alleged that some German tourists had parked their car and went to buy some meat at a local shop. This was on Monday, 27 May 2019 at about 07:00," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "When they came out of the shop, they discovered that their vehicle had been broken into and some of their belongings stolen. Capt Manatha said that the suspect was arrested early on Tuesday morning at a nearby informal settlements. "The belongings were recovered and handed over to the lawful owners." The suspect will appear before the Dutywa Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday on a charge of theft out of motor vehicle. Butterworth SAPS Cluster Commander, Brigadier Ngangema Xakavu, commended Dutywa police for their swift reaction in arresting the suspect and recovering their belongings. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  